{{Infobox lake | name = Katnosa | image = Katnosa.jpg | caption = Katnosa | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Nordmarka]] ([[Lunner]], [[Jevnaker]] and [[Ringerike (municipality)|Ringerike]]) | coords = {{coord|60|09|N|10|35|E|region:NO_type:waterbody_source:GNS-enwiki|display=title,inline}} | type = | inflow = | outflow = [[Katnoselva]] | catchment = | basin_countries = Norway | length = | width = | area = {{convert|2.2|km2|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = {{convert|464|m|abbr=on}} | frozen = | islands = | sections = | cities = }} '''Katnosa''' is a regulated lake in [[Nordmarka]], Norway bordering to the municipalities [[Lunner]], [[Jevnaker]] and [[Ringerike (municipality)|Ringerike]]. It drains through the river [[Katnoselva]] to the lakes [[Store Sandungen]], [[Hakkloa]], [[Bjørnsjøen]] and [[Skjærsjøen]]. It is regulated by the dam Katnosdammen from 1886. Katnosa is part of the [[Spålen–Katnosa Nature Reserve]].<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Katnosa |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://www.snl.no/Katnosa |language=Norwegian | accessdate=19 May 2012 }}</ref>
