'''Krichim Dam''' is a dam on the [[Vacha River]], [[Bulgaria]]. It is part of the [[Vacha Cascade Joint Implementation Project]] involving three more dams and four power stations.<ref name=Joint>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ji-cdm-austria.at/blueline/upload/vachacascadeeng3.pdf|title=Bulgarien: Vacha Cascade Joint Implementation Projekt |accessdate=11 September 2012|publisher= Energy industries – Renewable Sources}}</ref> The three existing dams on the [[Vacha River]] are the [[Vacha Dam]], [[Tsankov Dam]], and the [[Kamak Dam]]. The {{convert|105|m}} concrete dam was in its implementation stage as of 2011.<ref name="ICOLD">{{Cite web|url=http://www.hydroworld.com/index/display/article-display/355244/articles/hydro-review-worldwide/volume-16/issue-1/articles/icold-76supth-sup-annual-meeting-focus-on-dam-operations.html|title=ICOLD 76th Annual Meeting: Focus on Dam Operations|accessdate=11 September 2012|publisher= hydroworld.com}}</ref>

The dam supports the 80 MW [[Krichim Hydro Power Plant]]. 

