{{Orphan|date=April 2013}}
'''Non-Starchy Vegetables''' are [[vegetables]] that contain a lower amount of [[carbohydrates]] and [[calories]] compared to their [[starch]]y counterparts. Thus, for the same calories, one can eat a larger quantity of non-starchy vegetables compared to smaller servings of starchy vegetables.
