'''Olstappen''' is a [[lake]] in the municipalities of [[Sør-Fron]] and [[Nord-Fron]] in [[Oppland]] county, [[Norway]].

The [[Vinstra]] River, coming from the southwest, flows into the west side of Olstappen and flows out of Olstappen’s northeast corner, thence east into [[Gudbrandsdalslågen]] at the town of Vinstra.  The Espa River flows into Olstappen from the south, making it a tributary of the Vinstra.  Olstappen lies south of the town of Skåbu.

